items.text: I love this place. Great coffee, free WiFi, always bustling... Just find yourself a place to sit. I can usually find somewhere to sit, even when it's packed.
Try their cold brew coffee on a hot summer day. It's not on the menu but they're experimenting with it and will let you try if you ask.
Better than average coffee, but you pay for the privilege; £2.80 for a flat white is steep
Forget Starbucks and the other chains. Come on in! Real coffee and tasty buns
Awesome coffee!
Literally the best coffee in town!
Sit by the window and watch life go by!  Also, they have free wifi here. Just enter your name and email to log-in.
Great breakfast well executed coupled with happy staff and good coffee will make you happy foursure
Nice place, but with slightly surly service, and average coffee
The few decent places for coffee around Angel.
Amazing coffee, great space. Needs a better furniture setup
Avoid the croissants. Good coffee. Service is a bit disorganised but place is still new. Should get better!
Great coffee, industrial outside space :)
Tasty coffee with rich flavour in adequately amount. Not like SB sh**.  And the same for the homemade sandwiches.
I missed the atmosphere of London......    :(
Lovely coffee, terrible wifi.
The Raisin Brownie is divine.
The coffee is REALLY good, so don't be turned off by the ultra slow counter service.
If you dont order anything, it means you dont feel comfortable. They will ask you to leave if you do not order. Shame.
Tasty pain au raisin!
